ta. We observed a trend with [Fe/H] of 0.3 per dex when the effect of the\nmicroscopic diffusion is neglected in the recovery grid [...]. Therefore, any\nattempt to calibrate the mixing-length parameter by means of classical and\nasteroseimic observables of field stars seems to be statistically poorly\nreliable. As such, any claim about the dependence of the mixing-length on the\nmetallicity for field stars should be considered cautiously and critically.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 6 Feb 2019 17:01:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-03-06"}
