h 0.65 events expected from the estimated background,\nresulting in a lower limit on the $^{76}$Ge neutrinoless double-beta decay\nhalf-life of $2.7\\times10^{25}$ yr (90% CL) with a median sensitivity of\n$4.8\\times10^{25}$ yr (90% CL). Depending on the matrix elements used, a 90% CL\nupper limit on the effective Majorana neutrino mass in the range of 200-433 meV\nis obtained. The measured background in the low-background configurations is\n$11.9\\pm2.0$ counts/(FWHM t yr).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 6 Feb 2019 17:48:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-28"}
